raw_data.title: Business Analyst / System Analyst
raw_data.description:
Synthesizes complex or diverse information regarding the client's business needs. Collects and researches data for business case development. Analyzes and defines function requirements for new system or system improvements.
5 years’ experience working with customers representing various business functions and industries such as manufacturing, agricultural, high tech, financial, marketing, sales and merchandising to develop system requirements that are aligned with business goals. Must have successful experience collaborating with senior business and IT management to assist in current system assessments and 
	provide overall IT strategic direction. Requires competence in developing functional and design specifications, managing software development projects and writing proposals including project estimates. Must have experience working in a structured environment with a development methodology, data and process modeling skills, advanced writing skills, and meeting facilitation experience.
Bachelor’s degree in Computer Science or Management Information Systems or AA degree and three years’ work experience. Professional training in some or all of the following is preferred: Ecommerce, Customer Relationship Management, Supply Chain Management, Business Intelligence, Knowledge Management, and Enterprise Resource Planning.
